Clearly Asconius did not know, or Gallus would not have confided the secret to him; and if Asconius did not kn0W, we may be sure that no one else knew, and may well wonder why the family of Pollio had kept the secret so long.

This story of Asconius and Gallus, with the fact that the child was to be born in Pollio's consulship, was in my opinion what gave rise to the tradition, which has more generally found favour than any other, that the child was a son of Pollio.
